Botswana’s Economy Contracted 2.1% in Fourth Quarter After Mining Plunges

-- B y   N a s r e e n   S e r i a
-- 
2011-03-30T14:40:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/botswana-s-economy-contracted-2-1-in-fourth-quarter-after-mining-plunges.html
Botswana’s economy contracted an
annual 2.1 percent in the fourth quarter after mining output
plunged, the statistics office said.  Gross domestic product fell after expanding a revised 12.1
percent in the third quarter, the statistics office said in an
e-mailed statement today. Mining production dropped 22 percent
last quarter after rising 26 percent in the previous three
months, it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nasreen Seria at 
 nseria@bloomberg.net  